00:00:09.474 --> 00:00:12.383
- [Narrator] We are the paradoxical ape.

00:00:12.383 --> 00:00:13.622
Bipedal,

00:00:13.622 --> 00:00:14.910
naked,

00:00:14.910 --> 00:00:16.077
large brained,

00:00:17.667 --> 00:00:21.696
long the master of fire,
tools and language,

00:00:21.696 --> 00:00:25.940
but still trying to understand ourselves.

00:00:25.940 --> 00:00:29.261
Aware that death is inevitable,

00:00:29.261 --> 00:00:31.428
yet, filled with optimism.

00:00:32.646 --> 00:00:34.908
We grow up slowly.

00:00:34.908 --> 00:00:37.528
We hand down knowledge.

00:00:37.528 --> 00:00:39.611
We empathize and deceive.

00:00:40.907 --> 00:00:41.990
We shape the future

00:00:41.990 --> 00:00:45.490
from our shared understanding of the past.

00:00:46.513 --> 00:00:50.200
Carta brings together experts
from diverse disciplines

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:53.224
to exchange insights on who we are,

00:00:53.224 --> 00:00:54.891
and how we got here.

00:00:56.376 --> 00:01:00.080
An exploration made possible
by the generosity of humans

00:01:00.080 --> 00:01:00.913
like you.

00:01:15.202 --> 00:01:18.119
(electronic music)

00:01:20.598 --> 00:01:23.515
(electronic music)

00:01:39.634 --> 00:01:42.729
- [Ajit Varki] And so
we humans ask ourselves,

00:01:42.729 --> 00:01:43.646
who are we?

00:01:44.617 --> 00:01:47.184
What are we doing here?

00:01:47.184 --> 00:01:48.834
Where did we come from?

00:01:48.834 --> 00:01:50.233
How did we get here?

00:01:50.233 --> 00:01:52.606
And where are we going?

00:01:52.606 --> 00:01:56.828
As you know, Carta focuses
on two of these questions,

00:01:56.828 --> 00:01:59.490
in the form of the study of anthropogeny

00:01:59.490 --> 00:02:02.618
explaining the origin of humans.

00:02:02.618 --> 00:02:06.396
And we access all disciplines
that we can possibly access

00:02:06.396 --> 00:02:08.575
to interact, to come to some conclusions

00:02:08.575 --> 00:02:10.492
on these two questions.

00:02:11.673 --> 00:02:14.900
And this symposium is
co-sponsored by Carta and

00:02:14.900 --> 00:02:18.910
the KAVLI Institute for Brain and Mind.

00:02:18.910 --> 00:02:21.170
And we're a transdisciplinary
collaboration

00:02:21.170 --> 00:02:23.992
between faculty at UC San Diego and Salk,

00:02:23.992 --> 00:02:26.128
along with interested
scientists at other institutions

00:02:26.128 --> 00:02:29.161
and our mission is to explore
and explain the origins

00:02:29.161 --> 00:02:31.161
of the human phenomenon.

