00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:08.938
- [Tim White] Thank you,
good afternoon and welcome.

00:04:08.938 --> 00:04:10.688
On Sunday March 30th,

00:04:11.713 --> 00:04:12.546
1997,

00:04:13.904 --> 00:04:16.786
I received Professor Varki's announcement

00:04:16.786 --> 00:04:19.451
of something called Carta.

00:04:19.451 --> 00:04:20.820
The vision was ambitious-

00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:25.184
to create a unique, San
Diego-based enterprise

00:04:25.184 --> 00:04:29.475
to engage scholars and
students at the highest level

00:04:29.475 --> 00:04:32.367
across the wide range of
disciplines contributing

00:04:32.367 --> 00:04:36.284
knowledge about our place
in the natural world.

00:04:37.980 --> 00:04:41.796
Or, as the initial announcement put it,

00:04:41.796 --> 00:04:43.429
"the ultimate objective of the group

00:04:43.429 --> 00:04:45.104
"is to completely explain

00:04:45.104 --> 00:04:46.953
"the phenomenon of humans".

00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:49.106
(audience laughter)

00:04:49.106 --> 00:04:52.809
Now that was a tall
order even 21 years ago.

00:04:52.809 --> 00:04:53.892
Your presence here,

00:04:53.892 --> 00:04:56.134
and your presence online

00:04:56.134 --> 00:05:00.385
is one indicator of the
success of this enterprise.

00:05:00.385 --> 00:05:02.826
Carta's local and global
impacts have been impressive

00:05:02.826 --> 00:05:04.234
by any measure,

00:05:04.234 --> 00:05:07.102
making it a shining jewel in the crown of

00:05:07.102 --> 00:05:10.143
the University of California system.

00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:12.643
So Carta was launched in 1997.

00:05:14.985 --> 00:05:17.068
That was a decade

00:05:17.068 --> 00:05:19.985
before the first generation iPhone.

00:05:21.376 --> 00:05:23.913
And here we are today.

00:05:23.913 --> 00:05:26.096
I'm going to read a
passage from Stewart Brand,

00:05:26.096 --> 00:05:29.540
who you may know as the editor
of the Whole Earth Catalog,

00:05:29.540 --> 00:05:32.800
and President of the Long Now Foundation.

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:34.467
Brand wrote in 2011,

00:05:35.883 --> 00:05:37.763
"civilization is revving itself

00:05:37.763 --> 00:05:41.961
"into a pathologically
short attention span.

00:05:41.961 --> 00:05:44.671
"The trend might be coming from

00:05:44.671 --> 00:05:47.380
"the acceleration of technology,

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:52.032
"the short horizon perspective
of market-driven economics,

00:05:52.032 --> 00:05:56.633
"the next election
perspective of democracies,

00:05:56.633 --> 00:06:00.633
"or the distractions of
personal multi-tasking."

00:06:01.806 --> 00:06:05.486
That's your reminder to please
turn your cell phones off.

00:06:05.486 --> 00:06:08.970
(audience laughter)

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:11.470
That was only seven years ago.

00:06:14.761 --> 00:06:16.375
Today's invited speakers

00:06:16.375 --> 00:06:19.208
come from a wide range of disciplines.

00:06:19.208 --> 00:06:23.591
I'm going to illustrate a
bit of the temporal spectrum,

00:06:23.591 --> 00:06:25.174
that they'll cover.

00:06:26.063 --> 00:06:27.813
I'll start with this.

00:06:31.419 --> 00:06:33.450
This is a cobble.

00:06:33.450 --> 00:06:35.117
An original artifact

00:06:36.243 --> 00:06:39.493
from the bottom of a gorge in Tanzania.

00:06:40.777 --> 00:06:43.517
It was shaped by someone,

00:06:43.517 --> 00:06:45.350
1.8 million years ago,

00:06:47.471 --> 00:06:51.814
and it represents the
earliest technology made

00:06:51.814 --> 00:06:53.231
by our ancestors.

00:06:56.679 --> 00:06:59.012
Literally on the other hand,

00:07:01.382 --> 00:07:04.382
(audience laughter)

00:07:06.231 --> 00:07:07.064
This,

00:07:07.064 --> 00:07:10.134
is a now obsolete iPhone.

00:07:10.134 --> 00:07:13.134
(audience laughter)

00:07:17.758 --> 00:07:19.758
The range of technology.

00:07:22.386 --> 00:07:26.498
Today in the invaluable spaces
that Carta has established,

00:07:26.498 --> 00:07:29.843
we will be treated to
an intellectual banquet,

00:07:29.843 --> 00:07:34.843
that will reach far beyond
these two technological markers.

00:07:34.926 --> 00:07:37.442
On behalf of all of us here,

00:07:37.442 --> 00:07:39.362
and all of you out there online,

00:07:39.362 --> 00:07:43.130
let me thank the visionaries
who created Carta,

00:07:43.130 --> 00:07:45.865
and the supporters and students and staff

00:07:45.865 --> 00:07:47.711
whose efforts continue to make this broad,

00:07:47.711 --> 00:07:50.358
and productive intellectual space

00:07:50.358 --> 00:07:53.366
available to the widest audiences.

